and that right effort begins with what the Buddha called chaitanya it translates as will and in the standing meditation we came to that point where we could see intentions arise so just before we sat we noted intending to rise intending to sit now we could have stayed there we could have kept standing you don't have to obey an intention

106
00:11:46,384 --> 00:12:14,907
but as soon as you moved you empowered that intention and as soon as you do that you create a conditioning you've created what in the language is called a karma you hear this word karma which normally means your comeuppance but actually in the original literature it's what you do it's your action there's another word for your comeuppance so as soon as you as soon as you've put

107
00:12:15,292 --> 00:12:17,676
and you're willing to something, that's it.

108
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:18,557
